fields.name: iTOW
fields.description: GPS time of week of the navigation epoch from which the sync manager obtains the GNSS specific data. Like for the NAV message, the iTOW can be used to group messages of a single sync manager run together (See the description of iTOW for details)

fields.name: intDeltaFreq
fields.description: Frequency increment of the internal oscillator

fields.name: intDeltaFreqUnc
fields.description: Uncertainty of the internal oscillator frequency increment

fields.name: intRaw
fields.description: Current raw DAC setting commanded to the internal oscillator

fields.name: extDeltaFreq
fields.description: Frequency increment of the external oscillator

fields.name: extDeltaFreqUnc
fields.description: Uncertainty of the external oscillator frequency increment

fields.name: extRaw
fields.description: Current raw DAC setting commanded to the external oscillator

adjudication.reasoning: The extraction matches the standard u-blox 8 protocol definition for the UBX-TIM-FCHG message. The payload length of 32 bytes is correctly calculated based on the field widths, and the scaling factor of 2^-8 for the frequency fields is standard for this class of timing message. The reserved padding and byte alignment are also correct.
